  "lesson": {
    "title": "Transistor Switch",
    "description": "Press and hold the tact button: USB → 10kΩ → NPN base turns the transistor on. The east branch (USB → 470Ω → red LED → collector, emitter → ground) carries the LED current — the base only needs a small control current. Release the button and the LED goes off. Compare lesson 8 (button feeds the LED directly) and lesson 16 (pot sets the base threshold). NPN at 90°; LED at 90°."
